<br>
Completly empty this zone was. Mind you this wasnt during peak hours (around 1am). So theres probably no chance of me /ooc'ing for the Heart. So we left after about 30 mins (we were mainly lookin for exp).<br>
<br>
Question is... Can this quest be done by us (33 wiz 33 sham). My friend is very twinked, so he doesnt usually have too much problems tanking mobs. Also, is this WORTH taking valuble exp time to do. I do plan on Quad-kiting alot when I get to 34.<br>
<br>
Lastly, any tips on doing any part of this quest would be greatly appreiciated. Thank you for your time. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://houseofeq.d2g.com/earsig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rochenko>rochenko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 242<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/21/02 2:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SoTF (Flux) Questions and Tips?</span><hr size=1> I'd say you two could do ok in perma if he were 34 and had his pet, or if you brought a tank with you (preferable).  The mobs in there aren't particularly dificult, but they tend to swarm.  To get the heart of fire, you'll need a good group.  The goblins in Sol A swarm like crazy and are pretty nasty.  I was 30ish when I did this quest, and I had a 50 something pally helping me out...he got killed.  A full group in the low 30s should do fine though.  The staff is truly a wonderful tool for a wizard.  <br>
<br>
